# TS6 Manager — operator env file template.
#
# Copy to: $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/containers/systemd/ts6-manager.env
# (typically  ~/.config/containers/systemd/ts6-manager.env )
#
# Chmod 0600 — this file holds the JWT signing key and the at-rest
# encryption key. Never commit a populated copy.

# ─── REQUIRED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# JWT signing secret. The server refuses to boot with NODE_ENV=production
# unless this is set to a non-placeholder value of ≥ 32 bytes of entropy.
# Generate: openssl rand -base64 48
JWT_SECRET=

# ─── RECOMMENDED ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AES-256-GCM key for at-rest secret encryption (TS server-connection
# credentials, SSH host-key fingerprints, etc.). If unset the server
# falls back to deriving the key from JWT_SECRET — workable but means
# both secrets rotate together. Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
# ENCRYPTION_KEY=

# Public origin the browser hits the UI on. Used for CORS + cookie
# domain. Defaults to http://localhost:3000 in production mode.
# FRONTEND_URL=https://ts6.example.org

# ─── OPTIONAL TUNING ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Log verbosity (trace, debug, info, warn, error). Default: info.
# LOG_LEVEL=info

# Set to 1 for pretty-printed logs (dev only — prod stays JSON).
# LOG_PRETTY=1

# Number of trusted reverse-proxy hops in front of the listener
# (spec §6.8). 0 = direct exposure (ignore X-Forwarded-For).
# 1 = exactly one trusted proxy rewrote/appended the client IP.
# TRUSTED_PROXY_HOPS=0

# JWT lifetimes (15m / 7d / 30s / 2h syntax, or bare seconds).
# JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRY=15m
# JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRY=7d

# ─── SIDECAR (Phase 5 VIDEO) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Manager → sidecar HTTP control plane URL. When set, the manager
# routes video-source RPCs through it. Disable to hide the video UI.
# SIDECAR_URL=http://127.0.0.1:9800

# Publicly-reachable WebTransport endpoint advertised to the widget
# viewer (PURA-146). Must terminate TLS — browsers reject WebTransport
# on cleartext origins. Leave unset to show "No live video".
# MOQ_PUBLIC_URL=https://moq.example.org

# ─── YOUTUBE COOKIE FILE (music bot) ──────────────────────────────────
# YT_COOKIE_FILE=/var/lib/ts6-manager/cookies/youtube.txt

# ─── SSH BRIDGE (Phase 2 control-path) ────────────────────────────────
# Path to a shared OpenSSH known_hosts file. Empty/unset falls back to
# per-row fingerprint pinning.
# TS_SSH_KNOWN_HOSTS=/var/lib/ts6-manager/known_hosts

# Trust-on-first-use for SSH host keys (PURA-100). MitM-exposed on the
# first connect — pin the fingerprint out-of-band instead when possible.
# TS_SSH_TOFU=0

# Accept self-signed certificates on upstream TS WebQuery connections.
# Dev/lab only.
# TS_ALLOW_SELF_SIGNED=0

# ─── WIDGET RATE LIMITS (PURA-72 Slice F) ─────────────────────────────
# Per-token + per-IP request budgets (req/min) for /api/widget/*.
# WIDGET_RATE_LIMIT_PER_TOKEN_PER_MINUTE=30
# WIDGET_RATE_LIMIT_PER_IP_PER_MINUTE=30
